Grotto Runtime SDK — the game runs inside a Grotto host that provides trusted identity, cloud saves, events and leaderboards. Wire it, and DEGRADE GRACEFULLY (localStorage / no-ops) when `window.GrottoRuntime` is absent so the game still runs standalone:
  const grotto = await window.GrottoRuntime?.ready?.({ timeoutMs: 8000 }).catch(() => null);
  const player = grotto && await grotto.getPlayer();          // { id, displayName, wallet? }
  const save = grotto ? await grotto.loadSave('default', DEFAULT_STATE) : { state: DEFAULT_STATE };
  await grotto?.save('default', state);                       // cloud autosave
  await grotto?.submitScore(score, { board: 'default' });     // ranked leaderboard (server keeps best)
  const top = await grotto?.leaderboard({ board: 'default', limit: 10 }); // { entries:[{rank,wallet,score}] }
Never ask the client to prove who the player is — identity comes from the host session. Wire submitScore + leaderboard whenever the game has a score.
